title: Free Sports Physicals Hit a Homerun at Elkton High School
content: Union Hospital sets up student athletes for success in the new sports season

ChristianaCare Union Hospital recently provided free sports physicals at Elkton High School in Cecil County, Maryland, to over 500 student athletes for the upcoming sports season. Over 50 volunteers from Union Hospital, Cecil County Public Schools, West Cecil Health Center, Saint Francis Hospital and ATI Sports Medicine helped young people get assessed quickly and carefully. Thank you to our caregivers and community members who make this annual event possible for our future sports stars. We look forward to seeing our student athletes succeed!
